name: currency
documentation: Specifies the currency associated with the net price. This element is not present if the price is expressed in percentage terms (as specified through the priceExpression element).

name: amount
documentation: Specifies the net price amount. In the case of a fixed income security or a convertible bond, this price includes the accrued interests.

name: priceExpression
documentation: Specifies whether the price is expressed in absolute or relative terms.

name: initialFactor
documentation: The part of the mortgage that is outstanding on trade inception, i.e. has not been repaid yet as principal. It is expressed as a multiplier factor to the morgage: 1 means that the whole mortage amount is outstanding, 0.8 means that 20% has been repaid.

name: currentFactor
documentation: The part of the mortgage that is currently outstanding. It is expressed similarly to the initial factor, as factor multiplier to the mortgage. This term is formally defined as part of the "ISDA Standard Terms Supplement for use with credit derivatives transactions on mortgage-backed security with pas-as-you-go or physical settlement".

name: openUnits
documentation: The number of units (index or securities) that constitute the underlyer of the swap. In the case of a basket swap, this element is used to reference both the number of basket units, and the number of each asset components of the basket when these are expressed in absolute terms.

name: basketConstituent
documentation: Describes each of the components of the basket.

name: basketDivisor
documentation: Specifies the basket divisor amount. This value is normally used to adjust the constituent weight for pricing or to adjust for dividends, or other corporate actions.

name: basketVersion
documentation: Basket version, used to record changes in basket composition or weights

name: basketCurrency
documentation: Specifies the currency for this basket.

name: constituentWeight
documentation: Specifies the weight of each of the underlyer constituent within the basket, either in absolute or relative terms. This is an optional component, as certain swaps do not specify a specific weight for each of their basket constituents.

name: dividendPayout
documentation: Specifies the dividend payout ratio associated with an equity underlyer. A basket swap can have different payout ratios across the various underlying constituents. In certain cases the actual ratio is not known on trade inception, and only general conditions are then specified. Users should note that FpML makes a distinction between the derivative contract and the underlyer of the contract. It would be better if the agreed dividend payout on a derivative contract was modelled at the level of the derivative contract, an approach which may be adopted in the next major version of FpML.

name: underlyerPrice
documentation: Specifies the price that is associated with each of the basket constituents. This component is optional, as it is not absolutely required to accurately describe the economics of the trade, considering the price that characterizes the equity swap is associated to the leg of the trade.

name: underlyerNotional
documentation: Specifies the notional (i.e. price * quantity) that is associated with each of the basket constituents. This component is optional, as it is not absolutely required to accurately describe the economics of the trade, considering the notional that characterizes the equity swap is associated to the leg of the trade.

name: underlyerSpread
documentation: Provides a link to the spread schedule used for this underlyer.

name: couponPayment
documentation: The next upcoming coupon payment.

name: underlyerFinancing
documentation: Financing terms associated with this underlyer

name: underlyerLoanRate
documentation: Loan rate terms associated with this underlyer. Commonly used for stock loan. You must not duplicate data elements already contained within dividend conditions at transaction level

name: underlyerCollateral
documentation: Collateral associated with this underlyer. Note that this is not typical usage, collateral is more often at transaction level

name: parValue
documentation: Specifies the nominal amount of a fixed income security or convertible bond.

name: faceAmount
documentation: Specifies the total amount of the issue. Corresponds to the par value multiplied by the number of issued security.

name: instrumentId
documentation: Identification of the underlying asset, using public and/or private identifiers.

name: description
documentation: Long name of the underlying asset.

name: currency
documentation: The currency in which an amount is denominated.

name: commissionDenomination
documentation: The type of units used to express a commission.

name: commissionAmount
documentation: The commission amount, expressed in the way indicated by the commissionType element.

name: currency
documentation: The currency in which an amount is denominated.

name: commissionPerTrade
documentation: The total commission per trade.

name: fxRate
documentation: FX Rates that have been used to convert commissions to a single currency.

name: rateSource
documentation: The publication in which the rate, price, index or factor is to be found. (e.g Gas Daily, Platts Bloomberg.)

name: rateSourcePage
documentation: A specific page or screen (in the case of electronically published information) on which the rate source is to be found.

name: rateSourcePageHeading
documentation: The heading for the rate source on a given rate source page or screen.

name: openUnits
documentation: The number of units (index or securities) that constitute the underlyer of the swap. In the case of a basket swap, this element is used to reference both the number of basket units, and the number of each asset components of the basket when these are expressed in absolute terms.

name: basketPercentage
documentation: The relative weight of each respective basket constituent, expressed in percentage. A basket percentage of 5% would be represented as 0.05.

name: basketAmount
documentation: DEPRECATED. The relative weight of each respective basket constituent, expressed as a monetary amount.

name: underlyingEquity
documentation: Specifies the equity in which the convertible bond can be converted.

name: redemptionDate
documentation: Earlier date between the convertible bond put dates and its maturity date.

name: deliveryNearbyMultiplier
documentation: A time multiplier, e.g. 1, 2 or 3 etc. used in defining Delivery Nearby date.

name: deliveryNearbyType
documentation: Defines a type of the delivery nearby qualifier, expect to be used in conjunction with a delivery nearby multiplier, e.g. 1NearByMonth, 1NearbyWeek, etc. If 'CalculationPeriod' is used, the delivery nearby multiplier is expected to be '0'. To represent 'Spot', the value of the delivery nearby type should be 'NearbyMonth' and the delivery period multiplier should be set to '0' (zero).

name: term
documentation: Specifies the term of the deposit, e.g. 5Y.

name: paymentFrequency
documentation: Specifies the frequency at which the deposit pays, e.g. 6M.

name: dayCountFraction
documentation: The day count basis for the deposit.

name: dividendPayoutRatio
documentation: Specifies the total actual dividend payout ratio associated with the equity underlyer.

name: dividendPayoutRatioCash
documentation: Specifies the cash actual dividend payout ratio associated with the equity underlyer.

name: dividendPayoutRatioNonCash
documentation: Specifies the non cash actual dividend payout ratio associated with the equity underlyer.

name: dividendPayoutConditions
documentation: Specifies the dividend payout conditions that will be applied in the case where the actual ratio is not known, typically because of regulatory or legal uncertainties.

name: dividendPayment
documentation: The next upcoming dividend payment or payments.

name: constituentExchangeId
documentation: Identification of all the exchanges where constituents are traded. The term "Exchange" is assumed to have the meaning as defined in the ISDA 2002 Equity Derivatives Definitions.

name: multiplier
documentation: Specifies the contract multiplier that can be associated with the number of units.

name: contractReference
documentation: Specifies the contract that can be referenced, besides the undelyer type.

name: expirationDate
documentation: The date when the contract expires.

name: quotedCurrencyPair
documentation: Defines the two currencies for an FX trade and the quotation relationship between the two currencies.

name: fundManager
documentation: Specifies the fund manager that is in charge of the fund.

name: strike
documentation: Specifies the price at which the option can be exercised.

name: strikeCurrency
documentation: The currency in which the strike of the option is expressed.

name: strikeUnits
documentation: Units in which the option strike is expressed e.g. currency Amount, BasisPoints, Percentage, Rate. Reportable reference data under MiFID RTS 22

name: optionType
documentation: Specifies whether the option allows the holder to buy or sell tne underlying asset.

name: exerciseStyle
documentation: Specifies the exercise style of the option {American, Bermuda, European}

name: underlyer
documentation: Underlyer of the option e.g. a listed future.

name: settlementType
documentation: Settlement method for the contract (Cash, Physical). This value is used to populate the "Delivery Type" field for regulatory reporting (CFTC, ESMA).

name: multiplier
documentation: The multiplier is the minimum number of the underlying - index or stock - that a participant has to trade while taking a position in the Future contract. The purpose of the multiplier is to inflate the value of the contract to add leverage to the trade. The multiplier for the Dow is 10, for the Nasdaq it is 100 and it is 250 for the Standard and Poor's index.

name: futureContractReference
documentation: Native identifier for the contract on the listing exchange.

name: maturity
documentation: The date when the future contract expires.

name: contractYearMonth
documentation: The contract month of the futures contract. i.e. F13 WTI NYMEX Contract is 2013-01.

name: underlyer
documentation: Underlyer of the option e.g. a listed future.

name: settlementType
documentation: Settlement method for the contract (Cash, Physical). This value is used to populate the "Delivery Type" field for regulatory reporting (CFTC, ESMA).

name: fxRate
documentation: Specifies a currency conversion rate.

name: quotedCurrencyPair
documentation: Defines the two currencies for an FX trade and the quotation relationship between the two currencies.

name: rateSource
documentation: Defines the source of the FX rate.

name: currency
documentation: Trading currency of the underlyer when transacted as a cash instrument.

name: issuerPartyReference
documentation: Specifies the issuer name of a fixed income security or convertible bond. The name is specified as an href into one of the party blocks.

name: creditQuality
documentation: Credit quality type (e.g. SFTR specified types: 'INVG' - Investment grade; 'NIVG' - Non-investment grade; 'NOTR' - Non-rated). Classifies the risk of the security. Note: 'NOAP' - Not applicable value is indicated by the absence of the 'creditQuality' element.

name: maturity
documentation: Credit maturity. The date when the principal amount of a security becomes due and payable.

name: instrumentId
documentation: Identification of the underlying asset, using public and/or private identifiers.

name: instrumentType
documentation: Classification of the asset, using public and/or private typologies e.g. ISO 10962 CFI code.

name: description
documentation: Long name of the underlying asset.

name: futureId
documentation: A short form unique identifier for the reference future contract in the case of an index underlyer.

name: lien
documentation: Specifies the seniority level of the lien.

name: facilityType
documentation: The type of loan facility (letter of credit, revolving, ...).

name: maturity
documentation: The date when the principal amount of the loan becomes due and payable.

name: creditAgreementDate
documentation: The credit agreement date is the closing date (the date where the agreement has been signed) for the loans in the credit agreement. Funding of the facilities occurs on (or sometimes a little after) the Credit Agreement date. This underlyer attribute is used to help identify which of the company's outstanding loans are being referenced by knowing to which credit agreement it belongs. ISDA Standards Terms Supplement term: Date of Original Credit Agreement.

name: tranche
documentation: The loan tranche that is subject to the derivative transaction. It will typically be referenced as the Bloomberg tranche number. ISDA Standards Terms Supplement term: Bloomberg Tranche Number.

name: seniority
documentation: The seniority. E.g. senior, senior secured etc.

name: originalPrincipalAmount
documentation: The initial issued amount of the mortgage obligation.

name: pool
documentation: The morgage pool that is underneath the mortgage obligation.

name: sector
documentation: The sector classification of the mortgage obligation.

name: tranche
documentation: The mortgage obligation tranche that is subject to the derivative transaction.

name: openEndedFund
documentation: Boolean indicator to specify whether the mutual fund is an open-ended mutual fund.

name: fundManager
documentation: Specifies the fund manager that is in charge of the fund.

name: paymentDate
documentation: The date that the dividend or coupon is due.

name: amount
documentation: The amount of the dividend or coupon payment. Value of dividends or coupon between ex and pay date. Stock: if we are between ex-date and pay-date and the dividend is payable under the swap, then this should be the ex-div amount * # of securities. Bond: regardless of where we are vis-a-vis resets: (coupon % * face of bonds on swap * (bond day count fraction using days last coupon pay date of the bond through today).

name: accruedInterest
documentation: Accrued interest on the dividend or coupon payment. When the TRS is structured to pay a dividend or coupon on reset after payable date, you may earn interest on these amounts. This field indicates the interest accrued on dividend/coupon from pay date to statement date. This will only apply to a handful of agreements where dividendss are held to the next reset AND you receive/pay interest on unpaid amounts.

name: commission
documentation: This optional component specifies the commission to be charged for executing the hedge transactions.

name: determinationMethod
documentation: Specifies the method according to which an amount or a date is determined.

name: amountRelativeTo
documentation: The href attribute value will be a pointer style reference to the element or component elsewhere in the document where the anchor amount is defined.

name: cleanNetPrice
documentation: The net price excluding accrued interest. The "Dirty Price" for bonds is put in the "netPrice" element, which includes accrued interest. Thus netPrice - cleanNetPrice = accruedInterest. The currency and price expression for this field are the same as those for the (dirty) netPrice.

name: quotationCharacteristics
documentation: Allows information about how the price was quoted to be provided.

name: term
documentation: Specifies the term of the simple swap, e.g. 5Y.

name: paymentFrequency
documentation: Specifies the frequency at which the index pays, e.g. 6M.

name: dayCountFraction
documentation: The day count basis for the index.

name: paymentFrequency

name: startTerm

name: endTerm

name: depositoryReceipt
documentation: A Depository Receipt is a negotiable certificate issued by a trust company or security depository. This element is used to represent whether a Depository Receipt is applicable or not to the underlyer.

documentation: Describes the swap's underlyer when it has only one asset component.

name: basket
documentation: Describes the swap's underlyer when it has multiple asset components.

name: exchangeId
documentation: Identification of the exchange on which this asset is transacted for the purposes of calculating a contractural payoff. The term "Exchange" is assumed to have the meaning as defined in the ISDA 2002 Equity Derivatives Definitions.

name: clearanceSystem
documentation: Identification of the clearance system associated with the transaction exchange.

name: definition
documentation: An optional reference to a full FpML product that defines the simple product in greater detail. In case of inconsistency between the terms of the simple product and those of the detailed definition, the values in the simple product override those in the detailed definition.

name: basket
documentation: Defines the underlying asset when it is a basket.

name: bond
documentation: Identifies the underlying asset when it is a series or a class of bonds.

name: cash
documentation: Identifies a simple underlying asset type that is a cash payment. Used for specifying discounting factors for future cash flows in the pricing and risk model.

name: commodity
documentation: Identifies the underlying asset when it is a listed commodity.

name: convertibleBond
documentation: Identifies the underlying asset when it is a convertible bond.

name: curveInstrument
documentation: Defines the underlying asset when it is a curve instrument.

name: deposit
documentation: Identifies a simple underlying asset that is a term deposit.

name: equity
documentation: Identifies the underlying asset when it is a listed equity.

name: exchangeTradedFund
documentation: Identifies the underlying asset when it is an exchange-traded fund.

name: future
documentation: Identifies the underlying asset when it is a listed future contract.

name: fx
documentation: Identifies a simple underlying asset type that is an FX rate. Used for specifying FX rates in the pricing and risk model.

name: index
documentation: Identifies the underlying asset when it is a financial index.

name: loan
documentation: Identifies a simple underlying asset that is a loan.

name: mortgage
documentation: Identifies a mortgage backed security.

name: mutualFund
documentation: Identifies the class of unit issued by a fund.

name: option
documentation: Identifies the underlying asset when it is a listed option contract.

name: rateIndex
documentation: Identifies a simple underlying asset that is an interest rate index. Used for specifying benchmark assets in the market environment in the pricing and risk model.

name: security
documentation: Identifies a security of implicit type (derivable from the security reference data).

name: simpleCreditDefaultSwap
documentation: Identifies a simple underlying asset that is a credit default swap.

name: simpleFra
documentation: Identifies a simple underlying asset that is a forward rate agreement.

name: simpleIrSwap
documentation: Identifies a simple underlying asset that is a swap.

name: underlyingAsset
documentation: Define the underlying asset, either a listed security or other instrument.

name: warrant
documentation: Defines the underlying asset when it is a warrant.

name: basketName
documentation: The name of the basket expressed as a free format string. FpML does not define usage rules for this element.

name: specifiedPrice
documentation: The 'specified Price' describes the nature of the underlying price that is observed. It must be be stated in the underlyer definition as it is not defined in the Commodity Reference Price. Example values of 'specifiedPrice' are 'Settlement' (for a futures contract) and 'WeightedAverage' (for some published prices and indices).

name: deliveryDates
documentation: Deprecated: The 'deliveryDates' element is applicable for a Commodity Reference Price that references a listed future contract (e.g. The Delivery Date is a NearbyMonth).

name: deliveryNearby
documentation: A container for the parametric representation of nearby contracts.

name: deliveryDate
documentation: The Delivery Date is a fixed, single day.

name: deliveryDateYearMonth
documentation: The Delivery Date is a fixed, single month.

name: deliveryDateRollConvention
documentation: The 'deliveryDateRollConvention' specifies, for a Commodity Transaction that references a listed future via the 'deliveryDates' element, the day on which the specified future will roll to the next nearby month prior to the expiration of the referenced future. If the future will not roll at all - i.e. the price will be taken from the expiring contract, 0 should be specified here. If the future will roll to the next nearby on the last trading day - i.e. the price will be taken from the next nearby on the last trading day, then 1 should be specified and so on.

name: deliveryDateExpirationConvention
documentation: The 'deliveryDateExpirationConvention' specifies, for a Commodity Transaction that references a listed future via the 'deliveryDates' element, the day on which the specified future will expire ahead of the actual expiration of the referenced future. For example: Z21 Contract expires on 19Nov21, with an adjust of 2D the "expire" will be 16Nov21. DeliveryDateRollConvention takes precedence. Example: Pricing on the Z21 Contract with NearbyContractDay and a deliveryDateRoll of 10D, Sampling of the F22 Contract will occur on 8Nov21 through the last Date of the Z21 Contract. With an ExpConvention of 5D, the last sampling date on the F22 contract will be 12Nov21.

name: multiplier
documentation: The 'multiplier' specifies the multiplier associated with the Transaction. The 'multiplier' element has two uses: (1) for Freight Transactions or any Calculation Period specified for a Freight Transaction, if an amount is specified as the Multiplier then it is captured by this element and (2) if the Transaction is a heat rate option, the heat rate multiplier is represented in this element. If multiplier is not provided, multiplier is assumed to be 1. (i.e. rate source states 1 BBL of Oil as 90 Dollars. Multiplier of 10 will change the value to 900 dollars.)

name: commodityBase
documentation: A coding scheme value to identify the base type of the commodity being traded. Where possible, this should follow the naming convention used in the 2005 ISDA Commodity Definitions. For example, 'Oil'.

name: commodityDetails
documentation: A coding scheme value to identify the commodity being traded more specifically. Where possible, this should follow the naming convention used in the 2005 ISDA Commodity Definitions. For example, 'Brent'.

name: unit
documentation: A coding scheme value to identify the unit of measure (e.g. Therms) in which the undelryer is denominated. Where possible, this should follow the naming convention used in the 2005 ISDA Commodity Definitions.

name: currency
documentation: The currency in which the Commodity Reference Price is published (e.g. GBP).

name: exchangeId
documentation: For those commodities being traded with reference to the price of a listed instrument, the exchange where that instrument is listed should be specified in the 'exchange' element.

name: publication
documentation: For those commodities being traded with reference to a price distributed by a publication, that publication should be specified in the 'publication' element.

name: referenceEntity
documentation: The entity for which this is defined.

name: creditEntityReference
documentation: An XML reference a credit entity defined elsewhere in the document.

name: grossPrice
documentation: Specifies the price of the underlyer, before commissions.

name: netPrice
documentation: Specifies the price of the underlyer, net of commissions.

name: accruedInterestPrice
documentation: Specifies the accrued interest that are part of the dirty price in the case of a fixed income security or a convertible bond. Expressed in percentage of the notional.

name: fxConversion
documentation: Specifies the currency conversion rate that applies to an amount. This rate can either be defined elsewhere in the document (case of a quanto swap), or explicitly described through this component.

name: relatedExchangeId
documentation: A short form unique identifier for a related exchange. If the element is not present then the exchange shall be the primary exchange on which listed futures and options on the underlying are listed. The term "Exchange" is assumed to have the meaning as defined in the ISDA 2002 Equity Derivatives Definitions.

name: optionsExchangeId
documentation: A short form unique identifier for an exchange on which the reference option contract is listed. This is to address the case where the reference exchange for the future is different than the one for the option. The options Exchange is referenced on share options when Merger Elections are selected as Options Exchange Adjustment.

name: specifiedExchangeId
documentation: A short form unique identifier for a specified exchange. If the element is not present then the exchange shall be default terms as defined in the MCA; unless otherwise specified in the Transaction Supplement.

name: seniority
documentation: The repayment precedence of a debt instrument.

name: creditQuality
documentation: Credit quality type (e.g. 'INVG' - Investment grade; 'NIVG' - Non-investment grade; 'NOTR' - Non-rated). Classifies the risk of the security. Note: 'NOAP' - Not applicable value is indicated by the absence of the 'creditQuality' element.

name: creditRating
documentation: The credit rating.

name: couponType
documentation: Specifies if the bond has a variable coupon, step-up/down coupon or a zero-coupon.

name: couponRate
documentation: Specifies the coupon rate (expressed in percentage) of a fixed income security or convertible bond.

name: maturity
documentation: The date when the principal amount of a security becomes due and payable.

name: value
documentation: The value of the the quotation.

name: measureType
documentation: The type of the value that is measured. This could be an NPV, a cash flow, a clean price, etc.

name: quoteUnits
documentation: The optional units that the measure is expressed in. If not supplied, this is assumed to be a price/value in currency units.

name: side
documentation: The side (bid/mid/ask) of the measure.

name: currency
documentation: The optional currency that the measure is expressed in. If not supplied, this is defaulted from the reportingCurrency in the valuationScenarioDefinition.

name: currencyType
documentation: The optional currency that the measure is expressed in. If not supplied, this is defaulted from the reportingCurrency in the valuationScenarioDefinition.

name: timing
documentation: When during a day the quote is for. Typically, if this element is supplied, the QuoteLocation needs also to be supplied.

name: informationSource
documentation: The information source where a published or displayed market rate will be obtained, e.g. Telerate Page 3750.

name: time
documentation: When the quote was observed or when a calculated value was generated.

name: valuationDate
documentation: When the quote was computed.

name: expiryTime
documentation: When does the quote cease to be valid.

name: cashflowType
documentation: For cash flows, the type of the cash flows. Examples include: Coupon payment, Premium Fee, Settlement Fee, Brokerage Fee, etc.

name: businessCenter
documentation: A city or other business center.

name: exchangeId
documentation: The exchange (e.g. stock or futures exchange) from which the quote is obtained.

name: mimeType
documentation: Indicates the type of media used to provide the extra information. mimeType is used to determine the software product(s) that can read the content. MIME Types are described in RFC 2046.

name: string
documentation: Provides extra information as string. In case the extra information is in XML format, a CDATA section must be placed around the source message to prevent its interpretation as XML content.

name: hexadecimalBinary
documentation: Provides extra information as binary contents coded in hexadecimal.

name: base64Binary
documentation: Provides extra information as binary contents coded in base64.

name: originalMessage
documentation: Provides extra information as binary contents coded in base64.

name: requested
documentation: Whether the issuer of the financial instrument has requested or approved the trading or admission to trading of their financial instruments on a trading venue.

name: requestDate
documentation: Date and time of the request for admission to trading on the trading venue.

name: approvalDate
documentation: Date and time the issuer has approved admission to trading or trading in its financial instruments on a trading venue.

name: admissionDate
documentation: Date and time of the admission to trading on the trading venue or the date and time when the instrument was first traded or an order or quote was first received by the trading venue.

name: terminationDate
documentation: Date and time when the financial instrument ceases to be traded or to be admitted to trading on the trading venue.

name: name
documentation: The name of the algorithm.

name: role
documentation: The category of the function of the algorithm. The related individual performs the role specified in this field for the base party. For example, if the role is "Trader", the related person acts acts or acted as the base party's trader.

name: allocationTradeId
documentation: Unique ID for the allocation. Multiple allocation trade IDs are provided to allow for the use of USI/UTI representations along with party-specific trade identifiers.

name: allocatedFraction
documentation: The fractional allocation (0.45 = 45%) of the notional and "block" fees to this particular client subaccount.

name: allocatedNotional
documentation: The notional allocation (amount and currency) to this particular client account.

name: allocatingPartyReference
documentation: A pointer style reference to one of the parties to the trade, defined elsewhere in the document. The party referenced has requested its position in the trade to be allocated to several other parties or accounts.

name: type
documentation: The type of approval (e.g. "pre-clearing credit").

name: status
documentation: The current state of approval (.e.g preapproved, pending approval, etc.)

name: approver
documentation: The full name or identifiying ID of the relevant approver.

name: approvingPartyReference
documentation: A pointer style reference to a party defined elsewhere in the document. The party referenced has approved the specified item (e.g. trade or allocation).

name: approvedPartyReference
documentation: A pointer style reference to a party defined elsewhere in the document. The party referenced was approved for the specified item (e.g. trade or allocation) by the approving party (if specified).

name: approvalId
documentation: An identifer for a specific appoval, to allow the approval to be identified and tracked.

name: partyReference
documentation: A pointer style reference to a party identifier defined elsewhere in the document. The party referenced has allocated the contract identifier.

name: contractId
documentation: A contract id which is not version aware.

name: versionedContractId
documentation: A contract id which is version aware.

name: creditEvent
documentation: This element corresponds to the Credit Event Notice Delivered Under Old Transaction and Deemed Delivered Under New Transaction under the EXHIBIT C to 2004 ISDA Novation Definitions.

name: publiclyAvailableInformation
documentation: This element corresponds to the Notice of Publicly Available Information Delivered Under Old Transaction and Deemed Delivered Under New Transaction under the EXHIBIT C to 2004 ISDA Novation Definitions.

name: physicalSettlement
documentation: This element corresponds to the Notice of Intended Physical Settlement Delivered Under Old Transaction under the EXHIBIT C to 2004 ISDA Novation Definitions.

name: onBehalfOf
documentation: Indicates which party (and accounts) a trade is being processed for.

name: trade
documentation: The root element in an FpML trade document.

name: portfolio
documentation: An arbitary grouping of trade references (and possibly other portfolios).

name: creditDocument
documentation: What arrangements will be made to provide credit? (e.g. CSA, collateral pledge, guaranty, available resources, financing).

name: organizationCharacteristic
documentation: Allows the organization to specify which categories or characteristics apply to it for end-user exception determination. Examples include "FinancialEntity", "CaptiveFinanceUnit", "BoardOfDirectorsApproval".

name: transactionCharacteristic

name: calculationMethod
documentation: Specifies the type of calculation, e.g. whether the calculation is a compounding or an averaging calculation. This element distinguishes between the applicable subsections of Section 7 (7.3, 7.4, and 7.7). If the calculationMethod is Componding or Averaging, this implies that a daily compounded calculation will be done, i.e. that the underlying rate will be observed eacy applicalbe business day during the observation period and then compounded or averaged. If it is CompoundedIndex, this means that the rate administrator is doing the compounding each day and publishing the resulting index value. In this case the calculation agent is responsible for observing the index and the start and at the end of the observation period, and then backing out the implied rate by following the formula in section 7.7. (This formula divides the index value at the end by the index value at the beginning, subtracts 1, and then scales the resulting value based on the year fraction to annualize the rate.) In other words, for CompoundedIndex the observation frequency is effectively 1T, where for Compounding and Averaging, it is 1D.

In situation (i), the Independent Amount is not included in the calculation of Exposure, but in situation (ii), it is included in the calculation of Exposure. Thus, for situation (ii), the Independent Amount may be transferred along with any collateral call. Independent Amount is a defined term in the ISDA Credit Support Annex. This element must only be included when the offset is specified as a number of days. If the offset is zero days then the dayType element should not be included.

name: offset
documentation: Indicates whether time applies to the actual day specified (in which case this element should be omitted) the day prior to that day (in which case periodMultiplier should be -1 and period should be Day) or the day subsequent to that day (in which case periodMultiplier should be 1 and period should be Day).

name: partyReference
documentation: The party for which the message reciever should work.

name: accountReference
documentation: Identifies the account(s) related to the party when they cannot be determined from the party alone, for example in a inter-book trade.

name: identifier
documentation: An identifier that has been created to identify the agreement.

name: type
documentation: The agreement executed between the parties and intended to govern product-specific derivatives transactions between those parties.

name: version
documentation: The version of the agreement.

name: date
documentation: The date on which the agreement was signed.

name: groupType
documentation: Party Group Type, e.g. JointAndSeveralLiability

name: partyReference
documentation: Reference to a party that is a member of the group of entities that are acting together as a single party in a transaction.

name: paymentAmount
documentation: The currency amount of the payment.

name: paymentDate
documentation: The payment date. This date is subject to adjustment in accordance with any applicable business day convention.

name: paymentType
documentation: A classification of the type of fee or additional payment, e.g. brokerage, upfront fee etc. FpML does not define domain values for this element.

name: settlementInformation
documentation: The information required to settle a currency payment that results from a trade.

name: discountFactor
documentation: The value representing the discount factor used to calculate the present value of the cash flow.

name: presentValueAmount
documentation: The amount representing the present value of the forecast payment.

name: paymentDate
documentation: The payment date, which can be expressed as either an adjustable or relative date.

name: paymentDate
documentation: Payment date.

name: paymentAmount
documentation: A fixed payment amount.

name: paymentRule
documentation: A structure defining the calculation rule of the independent amount. Users are supposed to use type substitution at PaymentRule. PaymentRule is abstract and it is supposed to be substituted by PercentageRule. There is the expectation that other rules will be created in the future to model other types of independent amount payment rules.

name: paymentAmount
documentation: A fixed payment amount.

name: paymentReference
documentation: The reference to the identified payment strucutre.

name: grossCashflow
documentation: Payment details of this cash flow component, including currency, amount and payer/payee.

name: settlementInformation
documentation: The information required to settle a currency payment.

name: periodMultiplier
documentation: A time period multiplier, e.g. 1, 2 or 3 etc. A negative value can be used when specifying an offset relative to another date, e.g. -2 days.

name: period
documentation: A time period, e.g. a day, week, month or year of the stream. If the periodMultiplier value is 0 (zero) then period must contain the value D (day).

name: calculationPeriodFrequency
documentation: The frequency at which calculation period end dates occur with the regular part of the calculation period schedule and their roll date convention.

name: calculationPeriodDatesAdjustments
documentation: The business day convention to apply to each calculation period end date if it would otherwise fall on a day that is not a business day in the specified financial business centers.

name: honorific
documentation: An honorific title, such as Mr., Ms., Dr. etc.

name: firstName
documentation: Given name, such as John or Mary.

name: surname
documentation: Family name, such as Smith or Jones.

name: suffix
documentation: Name suffix, such as Jr., III, etc.

name: personId
documentation: An identifier assigned by a system for uniquely identifying the individual

name: businessUnitReference
documentation: The unit for which the indvidual works.

name: contactInfo
documentation: Information on how to contact the individual using various means.

name: dateOfBirth
documentation: The birth date of the person, e.g. 1970-01-01

name: country
documentation: The ISO 3166 standard code for the country where the individual works.

name: amount
documentation: The positive monetary quantity in currency units.

name: hourMinuteTime
documentation: A time specified in hh:mm:ss format where the second component must be '00', e.g. 11am would be represented as 11:00:00.

name: location
documentation: The geographic location to which the hourMinuteTime applies. The time takes into account any current day light saving changes or other adjustments i.e. it is the prevaling time at the location.

name: name
documentation: The name of the structure, e.g "USDLIBOR-3M EOD Curve".

name: currency
documentation: The currency that the structure is expressed in (this is relevant mostly for the Interes Rates asset class).

name: initialExchange
documentation: A true/false flag to indicate whether there is an initial exchange of principal on the effective date.

name: finalExchange
documentation: A true/false flag to indicate whether there is a final exchange of principal on the termination date.

name: intermediateExchange
documentation: A true/false flag to indicate whether there are intermediate or interim exchanges of principal during the term of the swap.

name: collateralValueAllocation
documentation: Collateral allocation by value.

name: currency1
documentation: The first currency specified when a pair of currencies is to be evaluated.

name: currency2
documentation: The second currency specified when a pair of currencies is to be evaluated.

name: quoteBasis
documentation: The method by which the exchange rate is quoted.

name: resetDate
documentation: The reset date.

name: adjustedFixingDate
documentation: The adjusted fixing date, i.e. the actual date the rate is observed. The date should already be adjusted for any applicable business day convention.

name: observedRate
documentation: The actual observed rate before any required rate treatment is applied, e.g. before converting a rate quoted on a discount basis to an equivalent yield. An observed rate of 5% would be represented as 0.05.

name: treatedRate
documentation: The observed rate after any required rate treatment is applied. A treated rate of 5% would be represented as 0.05.

name: observationWeight
documentation: The number of days weighting to be associated with the rate observation, i.e. the number of days such rate is in effect. This is applicable in the case of a weighted average method of calculation where more than one reset date is established for a single calculation period. If this element is not included, observationWeight = 1 by default.

name: rateReference
documentation: A pointer style reference to a floating rate component defined as part of a stub calculation period amount component. It is only required when it is necessary to distinguish two rate observations for the same fixing date which could occur when linear interpolation of two different rates occurs for a stub calculation period.

name: forecastRate
documentation: The value representing the forecast rate used to calculate the forecast future value of the accrual period.A value of 1% should be represented as 0.01

name: treatedForecastRate
documentation: The value representing the forecast rate after applying rate treatment rules. A value of 1% should be represented as 0.01

name: fallback
documentation: Observation Parameters for IBOR fallback rates. These allow recording information about how the fallback rate was

name: referenceBankId
documentation: An institution (party) identifier, e.g. a bank identifier code (BIC).

name: referenceBankName
documentation: The name of the institution (party). A free format string. FpML does not define usage rules for the element.

name: businessUnitReference
documentation: The unit that is related to this.

name: role
documentation: The category of the relationship. The related unit performs the role specified in this field for the base party. For example, if the role is "Trader", the related unit acts acts or acted as the base party's trading unit.

name: role
documentation: The category of the relationship. The related party performs the role specified in this field for the base party. For example, if the role is "Guarantor", the related party acts as a guarantor for the base party.

name: type
documentation: Additional definition refining the type of relationship. For example, if the "role" is Guarantor, this element may be used to specify whether all positions are guaranteed, or only a subset of them.

name: personReference
documentation: The individual person that is related to this.

name: role
documentation: The category of the relationship. The related individual performs the role specified in this field for the base party. For example, if the role is "Trader", the related person acts acts or acted as the base party's trader.

name: businessDayConvention
documentation: The convention for adjusting a date if it would otherwise fall on a day that is not a business day.

name: dateRelativeTo
documentation: Specifies the anchor as an href attribute. The href attribute value is a pointer style reference to the element or component elsewhere in the document where the anchor date is defined.

name: adjustedDate
documentation: The date once the adjustment has been performed. (Note that this date may change if the business center holidays change).

name: periodSkip
documentation: The number of periods in the referenced date schedule that are between each date in the relative date schedule. Thus a skip of 2 would mean that dates are relative to every second date in the referenced schedule. If present this should have a value greater than 1.

name: scheduleBounds
documentation: The first and last dates of a schedule. This can be used to restrict the range of values in a reference series of dates.

name: dateRelativeTo
documentation: Specifies the anchor as an href attribute. The href attribute value is a pointer style reference to the element or component elsewhere in the document where the anchor date is defined.

name: weeklyRollConvention
documentation: The day of the week on which a weekly reset date occurs. This element must be included if the reset frequency is defined as weekly and not otherwise.

name: resourceId
documentation: The unique identifier of the resource within the event.

name: resourceType
documentation: A description of the type of the resource, e.g. a confirmation.

name: language
documentation: Indicates the language of the resource, described using the ISO 639-2/T Code.

name: sizeInBytes
documentation: Indicates the size of the resource in bytes. It could be used by the end user to estimate the download time and storage needs.

name: length
documentation: Indicates the length of the resource. For example, if the resource were a PDF file, the length would be in pages.

name: mimeType
documentation: Indicates the type of media used to store the content. mimeType is used to determine the software product(s) that can read the content. MIME Types are described in RFC 2046.

name: name
documentation: The name of the resource.

name: comments
documentation: Any additional comments that are deemed necessary. For example, which software version is required to open the document? Or, how does this resource relate to the others for this event?

name: string
documentation: Provides extra information as string. In case the extra information is in XML format, a CDATA section must be placed around the source message to prevent its interpretation as XML content.

name: hexadecimalBinary
documentation: Provides extra information as binary contents coded in hexadecimal.

name: base64Binary
documentation: Provides extra information as binary contents coded in base64.

name: url
documentation: Indicates where the resource can be found, as a URL that references the information on a web server accessible to the message recipient.

name: lengthUnit
documentation: The length unit of the resource. For example, pages (pdf, text documents) or time (audio, video files).

name: lengthValue
documentation: The length value of the resource.

name: roundingDirection
documentation: Specifies the rounding direction.

name: precision
documentation: Specifies the rounding precision in terms of a number of decimal places. Note how a percentage rate rounding of 5 decimal places is expressed as a rounding precision of 7 in the FpML document since the percentage is expressed as a decimal, e.g. 9.876543% (or 0.09876543) being rounded to the nearest 5 decimal places is 9.87654% (or 0.0987654).

name: routingId
documentation: A unique identifier for party that is a participant in a recognized payment system.

name: routingIds
documentation: A set of unique identifiers for a party, eachone identifying the party within a payment system. The assumption is that each party will not have more than one identifier within the same payment system.

name: initialValue
documentation: The initial rate or amount, as the case may be. An initial rate of 5% would be represented as 0.05.

name: step
documentation: The schedule of step date and value pairs. On each step date, the associated step value becomes effective. A list of steps may be ordered in the document by ascending step date. An FpML document containing an unordered list of steps is still regarded as a conformant document.

name: standardSettlementStyle
documentation: An optional element used to describe how a trade will settle. This defines a scheme and is used for identifying trades that are identified as settling standard and/or flagged for settlement netting.

name: settlementInstruction
documentation: An explicit specification of how a currency payment is to be made, when the payment is not netted and the route is other than the recipient's standard settlement instruction.

name: settlementMethod
documentation: The mechanism by which settlement is to be made. The scheme of domain values will include standard mechanisms such as CLS, Fedwire, Chips ABA, Chips UID, SWIFT, CHAPS and DDA.

name: correspondentInformation
documentation: The information required to identify the correspondent bank that will make delivery of the funds on the paying bank's behalf in the country where the payment is to be made

name: intermediaryInformation
documentation: Information to identify an intermediary through which payment will be made by the correspondent bank to the ultimate beneficiary of the funds.

name: beneficiaryBank
documentation: The bank that acts for the ultimate beneficiary of the funds in receiving payments.

name: beneficiary
documentation: The ultimate beneficiary of the funds. The beneficiary can be identified either by an account at the beneficiaryBank (qv) or by explicit routingInformation. This element provides for the latter.

name: depositoryPartyReference
documentation: Reference to the depository of the settlement.

name: splitSettlement
documentation: The set of individual payments that are to be made when a currency payment settling a trade needs to be split between a number of ultimate beneficiaries. Each split payment may need to have its own routing information.

name: informationSource
documentation: The information source where a published or displayed market rate will be obtained, e.g. Telerate Page 3750.

name: cashSettlementReferenceBanks
documentation: A container for a set of reference institutions. These reference institutions may be called upon to provide rate quotations as part of the method to determine the applicable cash settlement amount. If institutions are not specified, it is assumed that reference institutions will be agreed between the parties on the exercise date, or in the case of swap transaction to which mandatory early termination is applicable, the cash settlement valuation date.

name: commencementDate
documentation: The first day of the exercise period for an American style option.

name: expirationDate
documentation: The last day within an exercise period for an American style option. For a European style option it is the only day within the exercise period.

name: latestExerciseTime
documentation: For a Bermuda or American style option, the latest time on an exercise business day (excluding the expiration date) within the exercise period that notice can be given by the buyer to the seller or seller's agent. Notice of exercise given after this time will be deemed to have been given on the next exercise business day.

name: latestExerciseTimeDetermination
documentation: Latest exercise time determination method.

name: paymentDate
documentation: The payment date. This date is subject to adjustment in accordance with any applicable business day convention.

name: splitSettlementAmount
documentation: One of the monetary amounts in a split settlement payment.

name: beneficiaryBank
documentation: The bank that acts for the ultimate beneficiary of the funds in receiving payments.

name: beneficiary
documentation: The ultimate beneficiary of the funds. The beneficiary can be identified either by an account at the beneficiaryBank (qv) or by explicit routingInformation. This element provides for the latter.

name: stepValue
documentation: The rate or amount which becomes effective on the associated stepDate. A rate of 5% would be represented as 0.05.

name: stepDate
documentation: The date on which the associated stepValue becomes effective. This day may be subject to adjustment in accordance with a business day convention.

name: streetLine
documentation: An individual line of street and building number information, forming part of a postal address.

name: strikeRate
documentation: The rate for a cap or floor.

name: buyer
documentation: The buyer of the option

name: seller
documentation: The party that has sold.

name: buyer
documentation: The buyer of the option

name: seller
documentation: The party that has sold.

name: stubStartDate
documentation: Start date of stub period. This was created to support use of the InterestRateStream within the Equity Derivative sphere, and this element is not expected to be produced in the representation of Interest Rate products.

name: stubEndDate
documentation: End date of stub period. This was created to support use of the InterestRateStream within the Equity Derivative sphere, and this element is not expected to be produced in the representation of Interest Rate products.

name: floatingRate
documentation: The rates to be applied to the initial or final stub may be the linear interpolation of two different rates. While the majority of the time, the rate indices will be the same as that specified in the stream and only the tenor itself will be different, it is possible to specift two different rates. For example, a 2 month stub period may use the linear interpolation of a 1 month and 3 month rate. The different rates would be specified in this component. Note that a maximum of two rates can be specified. If a stub period uses the same floating rate index, including tenor, as the regular calculation periods then this should not be specified again within this component, i.e. the stub calculation period amount component may not need to be specified even if there is an initial or final stub period. If a stub period uses a different floating rate index compared to the regular calculation periods then this should be specified within this component. If specified here, they are likely to have id attributes, allowing them to be referenced from within the cashflows component.

name: stubRate
documentation: An actual rate to apply for the initial or final stub period may have been agreed between the principal parties (in a similar way to how an initial rate may have been agreed for the first regular period). If an actual stub rate has been agreed then it would be included in this component. It will be a per annum rate, expressed as a decimal. A stub rate of 5% would be represented as 0.05.

name: stubAmount
documentation: An actual amount to apply for the initial or final stub period may have been agreed between th two parties. If an actual stub amount has been agreed then it would be included in this component.

name: clearedPhysicalSettlement
documentation: Specifies whether the swap resulting from physical settlement of the swaption transaction will clear through a clearing house. The meaning of Cleared Physical Settlement is defined in the 2006 ISDA Definitions, Section 15.2 (published in Supplement number 28).

name: predeterminedClearingOrganizationPartyReference
documentation: A reference to the clearing organization (CCP, DCO) to which the trade should be cleared. This is also known as the "Mutually Agreed Clearinghouse".

name: mutuallyAgreedClearinghouse
documentation: This may be used to specify a "mutually-agreed clearinghouse" for settlement.

name: agreedDiscountRate
documentation: This may be used to indicate the discount rate to be used for cash collateral for cash settlement purposes.

name: settlementRateSource
documentation: The method for obtaining a settlement rate. This may be from some information source (e.g. Reuters) or from a set of reference banks.

name: quotationRateType
documentation: Which rate quote is to be observed, either Bid, Mid, Offer or Exercising Party Pays. The meaning of Exercising Party Pays is defined in the 2000 ISDA Definitions, Section 17.2. Certain Definitions Relating to Cash Settlement, paragraph (j)

name: type
documentation: The type of telephone number (work, personal, mobile).

name: number
documentation: A telephonic contact.

name: fixedRate
documentation: The calculation period fixed rate. A per annum rate, expressed as a decimal. A fixed rate of 5% would be represented as 0.05.

name: spreadSchedule
documentation: The ISDA Spread or a Spread schedule expressed as explicit spreads and dates. In the case of a schedule, the step dates may be subject to adjustment in accordance with any adjustments specified in calculationPeriodDatesAdjustments. The spread is a per annum rate, expressed as a decimal. For purposes of determining a calculation period amount, if positive the spread will be added to the floating rate and if negative the spread will be subtracted from the floating rate. A positive 10 basis point (0.1%) spread would be represented as 0.001.

name: americanExercise
documentation: The parameters for defining the exercise period for an American style option together with any rules governing the notional amount of the underlying which can be exercised on any given exercise date and any associated exercise fees.

name: bermudaExercise
documentation: The parameters for defining the exercise period for a Bermuda style option together with any rules governing the notional amount of the underlying which can be exercised on any given exercise date and any associated exercise fees.

name: europeanExercise
documentation: The parameters for defining the exercise period for a European style option together with any rules governing the notional amount of the underlying which can be exercised on any given exercise date and any associated exercise fees.

name: exercise
documentation: An placeholder for the actual option exercise definitions.

name: product
documentation: An abstract element used as a place holder for the substituting product elements.

name: unadjustedDate
documentation: A date subject to adjustment.

name: dateAdjustments
documentation: The business day convention and financial business centers used for adjusting the date if it would otherwise fall on a day that is not a business date in the specified business centers.

name: adjustedDate
documentation: The date once the adjustment has been performed. (Note that this date may change if the business center holidays change).

name: businessCentersReference
documentation: A pointer style reference to a set of financial business centers defined elsewhere in the document. This set of business centers is used to determine whether a particular day is a business day or not.

name: buyerPartyReference
documentation: A reference to the party that buys this instrument, ie. pays for this instrument and receives the rights defined by it. See 2000 ISDA definitions Article 11.1 (b). In the case of FRAs this the fixed rate payer.

name: buyerAccountReference
documentation: A reference to the account that buys this instrument.

name: sellerPartyReference
documentation: A reference to the party that sells ("writes") this instrument, i.e. that grants the rights defined by this instrument and in return receives a payment for it. See 2000 ISDA definitions Article 11.1 (a). In the case of FRAs this is the floating rate payer.

name: sellerAccountReference
documentation: A reference to the account that sells this instrument.

name: allocationPartyReference
documentation: Reference to a party.

name: allocationAccountReference
documentation: Reference to an account.

name: floatingRateMultiplierSchedule
documentation: A rate multiplier or multiplier schedule to apply to the floating rate. A multiplier schedule is expressed as explicit multipliers and dates. In the case of a schedule, the step dates may be subject to adjustment in accordance with any adjustments specified in the calculationPeriodDatesAdjustments. The multiplier can be a positive or negative decimal. This element should only be included if the multiplier is not equal to 1 (one) for the term of the stream.

name: spreadSchedule
documentation: The ISDA Spread or a Spread schedule expressed as explicit spreads and dates. In the case of a schedule, the step dates may be subject to adjustment in accordance with any adjustments specified in calculationPeriodDatesAdjustments. The spread is a per annum rate, expressed as a decimal. For purposes of determining a calculation period amount, if positive the spread will be added to the floating rate and if negative the spread will be subtracted from the floating rate. A positive 10 basis point (0.1%) spread would be represented as 0.001.

name: rateTreatment
documentation: The specification of any rate conversion which needs to be applied to the observed rate before being used in any calculations. The two common conversions are for securities quoted on a bank discount basis which will need to be converted to either a Money Market Yield or Bond Equivalent Yield. See the Annex to the 2000 ISDA Definitions, Section 7.3. Certain General Definitions Relating to Floating Rate Options, paragraphs (g) and (h) for definitions of these terms.

name: capRateSchedule
documentation: The cap rate or cap rate schedule, if any, which applies to the floating rate. The cap rate (strike) is only required where the floating rate on a swap stream is capped at a certain level. A cap rate schedule is expressed as explicit cap rates and dates and the step dates may be subject to adjustment in accordance with any adjustments specified in calculationPeriodDatesAdjustments. The cap rate is assumed to be exclusive of any spread and is a per annum rate, expressed as a decimal. A cap rate of 5% would be represented as 0.05.

name: floorRateSchedule
documentation: The floor rate or floor rate schedule, if any, which applies to the floating rate. The floor rate (strike) is only required where the floating rate on a swap stream is floored at a certain strike level. A floor rate schedule is expressed as explicit floor rates and dates and the step dates may be subject to adjustment in accordance with any adjustments specified in calculationPeriodDatesAdjustments. The floor rate is assumed to be exclusive of any spread and is a per annum rate, expressed as a decimal. A floor rate of 5% would be represented as 0.05.

name: initialRate
documentation: The initial floating rate reset agreed between the principal parties involved in the trade. This is assumed to be the first required reset rate for the first regular calculation period. It should only be included when the rate is not equal to the rate published on the source implied by the floating rate index. An initial rate of 5% would be represented as 0.05.

name: finalRateRounding
documentation: The rounding convention to apply to the final rate used in determination of a calculation period amount.

name: averagingMethod
documentation: If averaging is applicable, this component specifies whether a weighted or unweighted average method of calculation is to be used. The component must only be included when averaging applies.

name: negativeInterestRateTreatment
documentation: The specification of any provisions for calculating payment obligations when a floating rate is negative (either due to a quoted negative floating rate or by operation of a spread that is subtracted from the floating rate).

name: floatingRateIndex
documentation: The ISDA Floating Rate Option, i.e. the name of the floating rate.

name: indexTenor
documentation: The ISDA Designated Maturity, i.e. the tenor of the floating rate.

name: observationCapRate
documentation: A maximum rate for an rate observation; optionally applied for daily averaged rates. These are described in the 2021 ISDA Definitions in Section 7.2.4

name: observationFloorRate
documentation: A minimum rate for an rate observation; optionally applied for daily averaged rates. These are described in the 2021 ISDA Definitions in Section 7.2.3

name: onBehalfOf
documentation: Indicates which party (or parties) (and accounts) a trade or event is being processed for. Normally there will only be a maximum of 2 parties, but in the case of a novation there could be a transferor, transferee, remaining party, and other remaining party. Also, in the context of a trade package there could be several parties for which limit check is requested, necessitating multiple onBehalfOf elements. Except for these cases, there should be no more than two onBehalfOf references in a message.

name: notionalReference
documentation: A pointer style reference to the associated notional schedule defined elsewhere in the document. This element has been made optional as part of its integration in the OptionBaseExtended, because not required for the options on securities.

name: integralMultipleAmount
documentation: A notional amount which restricts the amount of notional that can be exercised when partial exercise or multiple exercise is applicable. The integral multiple amount defines a lower limit of notional that can be exercised and also defines a unit multiple of notional that can be exercised, i.e. only integer multiples of this amount can be exercised.

name: minimumNotionalAmount
documentation: The minimum notional amount that can be exercised on a given exercise date. See multipleExercise.

name: minimumNumberOfOptions
documentation: The minimum number of options that can be exercised on a given exercise date.

name: party
documentation: A legal entity or a subdivision of a legal entity.

name: account
documentation: Optional account information used to precisely define the origination and destination of financial instruments.

name: partyId
documentation: A party identifier, e.g. a S.W.I.F.T. bank identifier code (BIC).

name: partyName
documentation: The legal name of the organization. A free format string. FpML does not define usage rules for this element.

name: contactInfo
documentation: Information on how to contact the party using various means.

name: businessUnit
documentation: Optional organization unit information used to describe the organization units (e.g. trading desks) involved in a transaction or business process .

name: person
documentation: Optional information about people involved in a transaction or busines process. (These are eomployees of the party).

name: partyReference
documentation: Reference to a party.

name: accountReference
documentation: Reference to an account.

name: classification
documentation: The party's industry sector classification.

name: creditRating
documentation: The party's credit rating.

name: country
documentation: The country where the party is domiciled.

name: region
documentation: A code for a grouping of countries to which this belongs.

name: jurisdiction
documentation: The legal jurisdiction of the entity's registration.

name: organizationType
documentation: The type of an organization's participantion in the OTC derivatives market.

name: payerPartyReference
documentation: A reference to the party responsible for making the payments defined by this structure.

name: payerAccountReference
documentation: A reference to the account responsible for making the payments defined by this structure.

name: discountFactor
documentation: The value representing the discount factor used to calculate the present value of the cash flow.

name: presentValueAmount
documentation: The amount representing the present value of the forecast payment.

name: startDate
documentation: Date on which this period begins.

name: endDate
documentation: Date on which this period ends.

name: premiumType
documentation: Forward start Premium type

name: pricePerOption
documentation: The amount of premium to be paid expressed as a function of the number of options.

name: percentageOfNotional
documentation: The amount of premium to be paid expressed as a percentage of the notional value of the transaction. A percentage of 5% would be expressed as 0.05.

name: primaryAssetClass
documentation: A classification of the most important risk class of the trade. FpML defines a simple asset class categorization using a coding scheme.

name: secondaryAssetClass
documentation: A classification of additional risk classes of the trade, if any. FpML defines a simple asset class categorization using a coding scheme.

name: productType
documentation: A classification of the type of product. FpML defines a simple product categorization using a coding scheme.

name: productId
documentation: A product reference identifier. The product ID is an identifier that describes the key economic characteristics of the trade type, with the exception of concepts such as size (notional, quantity, number of units) and price (fixed rate, strike, etc.) that are negotiated for each transaction. It can be used to hold identifiers such as the "UPI" (universal product identifier) required by certain regulatory reporting rules. It can also be used to hold identifiers of benchmark products or product temnplates used by certain trading systems or facilities. FpML does not define the domain values associated with this element. Note that the domain values for this element are not strictly an enumerated list.

name: assetClass
documentation: A classification of the risk class of the trade. FpML defines a simple asset class categorization using a coding scheme.

name: receiverPartyReference
documentation: A reference to the party that receives the payments corresponding to this structure.

name: receiverAccountReference
documentation: A reference to the account that receives the payments corresponding to this structure.

name: routingName
documentation: A real name that is used to identify a party involved in the routing of a payment.

name: routingAddress
documentation: A physical postal address via which a payment can be routed.

name: routingAccountNumber
documentation: An account number via which a payment can be routed.

name: routingReferenceText
documentation: A piece of free-format text used to assist the identification of a party involved in the routing of a payment.

name: routingIds
documentation: A set of unique identifiers for a party, eachone identifying the party within a payment system. The assumption is that each party will not have more than one identifier within the same payment system.

name: routingExplicitDetails
documentation: A set of details that is used to identify a party involved in the routing of a payment when the party does not have a code that identifies it within one of the recognized payment systems.

name: routingIdsAndExplicitDetails
documentation: A combination of coded payment system identifiers and details for physical addressing for a party involved in the routing of a payment.

name: settlementAmount
documentation: Settlement Amount

name: settlementCurrency
documentation: Settlement Currency for use where the Settlement Amount cannot be known in advance

name: lossOfStockBorrow

name: fallbackRate

name: numberOfUnits

name: unitPrice

name: priceExpression

name: initialFactor
documentation: The part of the mortgage that is outstanding on trade inception, i.e. has not been repaid yet as principal. It is expressed as a multiplier factor to the morgage: 1 means that the whole mortage amount is outstanding, 0.8 means that 20% has been repaid.

name: currentFactor
documentation: The part of the mortgage that is currently outstanding. It is expressed similarly to the initial factor, as factor multiplier to the mortgage. name: openUnits

name: basketConstituent

name: basketVersion

name: basketCurrency

name: constituentWeight
documentation: Specifies the weight of each of the underlyer constituent within the basket, either in absolute or relative terms. This is an optional component, as certain swaps do not specify a specific weight for each of their basket constituents.

name: dividendPayout
documentation: Specifies the dividend payout ratio associated with an equity underlyer. A basket swap can have different payout ratios across the various underlying constituents. In certain cases the actual ratio is not known on trade inception, and only general conditions are then specified. Users should note that FpML makes a distinction between the derivative contract and the underlyer of the contract. It would be better if the agreed dividend payout on a derivative contract was modelled at the level of the derivative contract, an approach which may be adopted in the next major version of FpML.

name: underlyerPrice
documentation: Specifies the price that is associated with each of the basket constituents. This component is optional, as it is not absolutely required to accurately describe the economics of the trade, considering the price that characterizes the equity swap is associated to the leg of the trade.

name: underlyerNotional
documentation: Specifies the notional (i.e. price * quantity) that is associated with each of the basket constituents. documentation: The 'deliveryDateRollConvention' specifies, for a Commodity Transaction that references a listed future via the 'deliveryDates' element, the day on which the specified future will roll to the next nearby month prior to the expiration of the referenced future. If the future will not roll at all - i.e. the price will be taken from the expiring contract, 0 should be specified here. If the future will roll to the next nearby on the last trading day - i.e. the price will be taken from the next nearby on the last trading day, then 1 should be specified and so on.

name: deliveryDateExpirationConvention
documentation: The 'deliveryDateExpirationConvention' specifies, for a Commodity Transaction that references a listed future via the 'deliveryDates' element, the day on which the specified future will expire ahead of the actual expiration of the referenced future. For example: Z21 Contract expires on 19Nov21, with an adjust of 2D the "expire" will be 16Nov21. DeliveryDateRollConvention takes precedence. Example: Pricing on the Z21 Contract with NearbyContractDay and a deliveryDateRoll of 10D, Sampling of the F22 Contract will occur on 8Nov21 through the last Date of the Z21 Contract. With an ExpConvention of 5D, the last sampling date on the F22 contract will be 12Nov21.

name: multiplier

The 'multiplier' element has two uses: (1) for Freight Transactions or any Calculation Period specified for a Freight Transaction, if an amount is specified as the Multiplier then it is captured by this element and (2) if the Transaction is a heat rate option, the heat rate multiplier is represented in this element. If multiplier is not provided, multiplier is assumed to be 1. (i.e. rate source states 1 BBL of Oil as 90 Dollars. Multiplier of 10 will change the value to 900 dollars.)

name: relativeDates
documentation: A series of dates specified as some offset to another series of dates (the anchor dates).

name: relativeDateAdjustments
documentation: The business day convention and financial business centers used for adjusting the relative date if it would otherwise fall on a day that is not a business date in the specified business centers.

name: commencementDate
documentation: The first day of the exercise period for an American style option.

name: expirationDate
documentation: The last day within an exercise period for an American style option. For a European style option it is the only day within the exercise period.

name: relevantUnderlyingDate
documentation: The date on the underlying set by the exercise of an option. What this date is depends on the option (e.g. in a swaption it is the swap effective date, in an extendible/cancelable provision it is the swap termination date).

name: earliestExerciseTime
documentation: The earliest time at which notice of exercise can be given by the buyer to the seller (or seller's agent) i) on the expriation date, in the case of a European style option, (ii) on each bermuda option exercise date and the expiration date, in the case of a Bermuda style option the commencement date to, and including, the expiration date , in the case of an American option.

name: latestExerciseTime
documentation: For a Bermuda or American style option, the latest time on an exercise business day (excluding the expiration date) within the exercise period that notice can be given by the buyer to the seller or seller's agent. Notice of exercise given after this time will be deemed to have been given on the next exercise business day.

name: expirationTime
documentation: The latest time for exercise on expirationDate.

name: multipleExercise
documentation: As defined in the 2000 ISDA Definitions, Section 12.4. Multiple Exercise, the buyer of the option has the right to exercise all or less than all the unexercised notional amount of the underlying swap on one or more days in the exercise period, but on any such day may not exercise less than the minimum notional amount or more that the maximum notional amount, and if an integral multiple amount is specified, the notional amount exercised must be equal to, or be an intergral multiple of, the integral multiple amount.

name: exerciseFeeSchedule
documentation: The fees associated with an exercise date. The fees are conditional on the exercise occuring. The fees can be specified as actual currency amounts or as percentages of the notional amount being exercised.

name: currency
documentation: The currency in which an amount is denominated.

name: thresholdRate
documentation: A threshold rate. The threshold of 0.10% would be represented as 0.001

name: limitationPercentage
documentation: Specifies the limitation percentage in Average Daily trading volume. A value expressed in percentage units i.e. 5 means 5%.

name: limitationPeriod
documentation: Specifies the limitation period for Average Daily trading volume in number of days.

name: beneficiaryPartyReference
documentation: Link to the party acting as beneficiary. This element can only appear within the beneficiary container element.

name: bermudaExerciseDates
documentation: The dates the define the Bermuda option exercise dates and the expiration date. The last specified date is assumed to be the expiration date. The dates can either be specified as a series of explicit dates and associated adjustments or as a series of dates defined relative to another schedule of dates, for example, the calculation period start dates. Where a relative series of dates are defined the first and last possible exercise dates can be separately specified.

name: relevantUnderlyingDate
documentation: The date on the underlying set by the exercise of an option. What this date is depends on the option (e.g. in a swaption it is the swap effective date, in an extendible/cancelable provision it is the swap termination date).

name: brokerConfirmationType

name: hourMinuteTime
documentation: A time specified in hh:mm:ss format where the second component must be '00', e.g. 11am would be represented as 11:00:00.

name: businessDayConvention
